    "body": "@elina2015 @iurimatias \r\n\r\nHmm, I haven't found designs for this.\r\nThe only thing I found is mobile (probably old) design here: https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=7703%3A2309\r\nTo show that \"current used reacted\", the whole background is changed there, not just border highlight.\r\n\r\nImplementing border for rectangles with different radiuses on corners is a quite tricky in QML.\r\nThere is a simple way of doing this (as it's done now). But as we see, it's not quite beautiful.\r\n\r\nOfc, it's possible to implement it well, but it's not quite easy.\r\nMaybe we should implement it with filling the background?",
